-- U.K. Stocks Fluctuate Before Federal Reserve Statement
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2012-09-13T13:51:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-13/u-k-stocks-fluctuate-before-federal-reserve-statement.html
U.K. stocks swung between gains and
losses as investors awaited a Federal Reserve announcement that
may initiate a new round of bond buying.  The FTSE 100 Index rose 0.2 percent to 5,791.96 at 2:48
p.m. in  London  after earlier rising as much as 0.3 percent and
falling as much as 0.2 percent.  The Fed will probably announce a third round of bond
purchases to stimulate the economy, according to almost two-
thirds of economists in a Bloomberg survey. The central bank
bought $2.3 trillion of bonds in two previous rounds of
quantitative easing.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  